Internet Protocol Version 6 (IPv6)
Addressing Architecture
2003", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC3513.html", target="_top", tooltip="This specification defines the addressing architecture of the IP Version 6 (IPv6) protocol.  The document includes the IPv6 addressing model, text representations of IPv6 addresses, definition of IPv6 unicast addresses, anycast addresses, and multicast addresses, and an IPv6 node's required addresses. [STANDARDS-TRACK]"];
  cites -> RFC3513;
  RFC4391 [label="RFC4391
Transmission of IP over InfiniBand
(IPoIB)
2006", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC4391.html", target="_top", tooltip="This document specifies a method for encapsulating and transmitting IPv4/IPv6 and Address Resolution Protocol (ARP) packets over InfiniBand (IB).  It describes the link-layer address to be used when resolving the IP addresses in IP over InfiniBand (IPoIB) subnets.  The document also describes the mapping from IP multicast addresses to InfiniBand multicast addresses.  In addition, this document defines the setup and configuration of IPoIB links. [STANDARDS-TRACK]"];
  cites -> RFC4391;
